How to generate sequence diagrams from the source in this directory
===================================================================

1. Install the GNU plotutils package from http://www.gnu.org/software/plotutils

2. Install UMLGraph from http://www.umlgraph.org, for example:

   wget 'http://www.umlgraph.org/UMLGraph-5.2.tar.gz'
   tar -xvzf UMLGraph-5.2.tar.gz

3. Create a symbolic link to the pic2plot macros from UMLGraph for generating
   UML sequence diagrams:

   ln -s UMLGraph-5.2/src/sequence.pic sequence.pic

3. Run pic2plot to generate the sequence diagrams:

   pic2plot -T ps tpread.pic           > tpread.ps
   pic2plot -T ps tpwrite.pic          > tpwrite.ps
   pic2plot -T ps stager_recall.pic    > stager_recall.ps
   pic2plot -T ps stager_migration.pic > stager_migration.ps
   pic2plot -T ps aggregator.pic       > aggregator.ps

4. Run gv to view the sequence diagrams:

   gv tpread.ps
   gv tpwrite.ps
   gv stager_recall.ps
   gv stager_migration.ps
   gv aggregator.ps
